Vice President Kamala Harris met with Prime Minister Boris Johnson of the United Kingdom to discuss the strong relationship between the two countries. They talked about various global challenges and opportunities, expressing their desire to strengthen the relationship and expand economic cooperation. They also discussed cooperation in areas such as global health, girls' education, and the environment. Vice President Harris thanked Prime Minister Johnson for the UK's contributions in Afghanistan and its leadership in combating climate change. They also discussed the need for coordinated international efforts to address migration and the root causes of it.